sing will continue normal operations  including food service Employees who do not work after    a m  must use personal time off or take an excused  unpaid absence For more information on weather related policies uic edu ExtremeWeather html https   vcas uic edu ExtremeWeather html Updates will be provided to the campus as needed via Urgent e mail  sms text messaging to subscribed mobile phones  the UIC edu website  social media  and the UIC Information Line                  nDec n   n     n  nPublic Safety Advisory n Public Safety Advisory Uncategorized On Sunday  Dec      around      p m  three juvenile victims exited a business on S  Halsted St  when they noticed several individuals lingering outside  The victims were followed by the offenders as they began to walk northbound on S  Halsted St  As they approached      S  Halsted St  a physical altercation occurred and the offenders demanded property from the victims  The offenders fled eastbound on Roosevelt Rd  with property from the victims  There are no reported injuries  The victims are not affiliated with UIC    The four offenders are described as   Male    feet   inches tall        years old  wearing a red sweatshirt and black runner mask  Male    feet   inches tall        years old  wearing a grey runner mask  Male  no specific age or height available  short black hair  wearing a puffy black jacket  Male  no specific descriptive information available  The Chicago Police Department will lead the investigation  Anyone with information should call        Approximate crime location mapped  goo  Use all your senses to be alert for danger  and when walking alone  look for the location of the nearest emergency call box  there are more than       across campus  call                for emergencies or                for non emergencies  UIC Police may also issue notifications for off campus crimes in the interest of public safety awareness  Security tips are standard precautions  not special or incident specific measur